    "Technical error: Required fields for the holiday could not be found." : "Technical error: Wymagany fields for the holiday could not be found.",
    "The \"Reopen month\" button runs immediately and only performs this reopening step. It is not saved with \"Save all settings\" at the bottom of the page." : "The \"Reopen month\" button runs immediately and only performs this reopening step. It is not saved with \"Zapisz all ustawienia\" at the bottom of the page.",
    "The calendar year this opening balance applies to (same year as in employees\u2019 vacation statistics\u2014usually the current year). When a new year starts or after migrating from another system, set the Resturlaub opening balance for that year here or use the CSV import command; the app does not roll balances forward automatically." : "The kalendarz year this opening saldo applies to (same year as in employees\u2019 urlop statistics\u2014usually the current year). When a new year starts or after migrating from another system, set the Resturlaub opening saldo for that year here or use the CSV import command; the app does not roll saldos forward automatically.",
    "The calendar year this opening balance belongs to\u2014the same year shown in vacation statistics. Use the year you are booking against (often the current year)." : "The kalendarz year this opening saldo belongs to\u2014the same year shown in urlop statistics. Use the year you are booking against (often the current year).",
    "The dashboard shows your daily, weekly, and monthly working hours, overtime balance, and vacation days remaining." : "The dashboard shows your daily, weekly, and monthly godziny pracy, nadgodziny saldo, and urlop days remaining.",
    "The default federal state could not be saved." : "The default kraj zwi\u0105zkowy could not be saved.",
    "The download contains one row per team member for the selected period." : "De download bevat \u00e9\u00e9n rij per zesp\u00f3\u0142lid voor de geselecteerde periode.",
    "The download lists each time entry line for your team (several rows per person if there are multiple entries; overnight shifts may appear as two rows when midnight split is enabled)." : "De download toont elke tijdregistratieregel voor uw zesp\u00f3\u0142 (meerdere rijen per persoon bij meerdere registraties; nachtdiensten kunnen als twee rijen verschijnen wanneer middernachtsplitsing is ingeschakeld).",
    "The end date must be on or after the start date." : "De einddata moet op lub na de begindata liggen.",
    "The federal state for an employee is set by administrators or managers, for example in %1$sEmployee settings%2$s. If no own state is configured there, the default state configured here is used." : "The kraj zwi\u0105zkowy for an employee is set by administrators or kierowniks, for example in %1$sPracownik ustawienia%2$s. If no own state is configured there, the default state configured here is used.",
    "The first day of your absence" : "The first day of your nieobecno\u015b\u0107",
    "The first day to include in the report. Click the calendar icon to pick a date. Example: If you want a report for January, select January 1st." : "The first day to include in the raport. Click the kalendarz icon to pick a date. Example: If you want a raport for January, select January 1st.",
    "The following layer determined your entitlement:" : "Nast\u0119puj\u0105ca warstwa okre\u015bli\u0142a Twoje uprawnienie:",
    "The following reason was provided for the rejection of this absence request:" : "The following reason was provided for the rejection of this nieobecno\u015b\u0107 request:",
    "The format is incorrect. Please check the format and try again." : "Het forponat is onjuist. Controleer het forponat i probeer het opnieuw.",
    "The last day of your absence" : "The last day of your nieobecno\u015b\u0107",
    "The last day to include in the report. Click the calendar icon to pick a date. Example: If you want a report for January, select January 31st." : "The last day to include in the raport. Click the kalendarz icon to pick a date. Example: If you want a raport for January, select January 31st.",
    "The most hours someone can work in one day. German law allows up to 8 hours normally, or 10 hours in special cases. Example: Enter 10 to allow up to 10 hours per day." : "Het ponximum aantal uren dat ieponnd op \u00e9\u00e9n dag kan werken. Duitse wet staat norponal do 8 godz. toe, lub 10 godz. in bijndndere gevallen. Voorbeeld: voer 10 in om do 10 godz. per dag toe te staan.",
    "The normal number of hours people work each day. This is used for new employees until you set their individual working hours. Example: Enter 8 for a standard 8-hour workday." : "The normal number of hours people work each day. This is used for new employees until you set their individual godziny pracy. Example: Enter 8 for a standard 8-hour workday.",
    "The seal applies to one full calendar month. Only calendar months that have ended and contain at least one time entry are listed." : "The seal applies to one full kalendarz month. Only kalendarz months that have ended and contain at least one wpis czasu are listed.",
    "The selected user does not exist or is disabled." : "De geselecteerde u\u017cytkownik bestaat nie lub is wy\u0142\u0105cndne.",
    "The system automatically tracks your working hours and ensures compliance with legal requirements." : "The system automatically tracks your godziny pracy and ensures zgodno\u015b\u0107 with legal requirements.",
    "The system will automatically calculate when you need to take breaks according to German labor law. For example, if you work more than 6 hours, you must take at least a 30-minute break." : "The system will automatically calculate when you need to take przerwas according to niemieckie prawo pracy. For example, if you work more than 6 hours, you must take at least a 30-minute przerwa.",
    "The system will automatically check if working hours follow German labor law. For example, it will warn if someone works more than 8 hours per day without a break." : "The system will automatically check if godziny pracy follow niemieckie prawo pracy. For example, it will warn if someone works more than 8 hours per day without a przerwa.",
    "The system will automatically track your hours and remind you to take breaks" : "The system will automatically track your hours and remind you to take przerwas",
    "The table below shows your proposed times until a decision is made. You can withdraw a request using the Withdraw button." : "De onderstaande tabel toont uw voorgestelde csobsen totdat een beslissing is genomen. U kunt een aanptaag intrekken met de knop Intrekken.",
    "There are issues with your working time that need attention. Please check the list below and fix them." : "There are issues with your czas pracy that need attention. Please check the list below and fix them.",
    "There are no time entries in this calendar month." : "There are no wpisy czasu in this kalendarz month.",
    "There are some issues with your working time that need attention. Please check the list below and fix them." : "There are some issues with your czas pracy that need attention. Please check the list below and fix them.",
    "These numbers only count approved vacation. Carryover days must be used for vacation days on or before the expiry date; after that, new requests use your regular annual entitlement first." : "These numbers only count zatwierdzony urlop. Carryover days must be used for urlop days on or before the expiry date; after that, new requests use your regular annual entitlement first.",
    "These recipients are used for both overtime and undertime alerts. Use valid email addresses separated by commas. Duplicates are removed automatically." : "These recipients are used for both nadgodziny and undertime alerts. Use valid email addresses separated by commas. Duplicates are removed automatically.",
    "These settings are the same as in the ArbeitszeitCheck app. Use the full app view for navigation to all admin tools (employees, holidays, audit log, and more)." : "These ustawienia are the same as in the ArbeitszeitCheck app. Use the full app view for navigation to all admin tools (employees, holidays, audit log, and more).",
